    "narrative": "The centerpiece of our offense today is **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, who boasts an elite 81.68 score. He remains our primary engine against Corbin, benefiting from a rare combination of park factors, positive platoon splits, and the high-percentage stolen base opportunity created by the opposing pitcher's slow delivery. We are also leaning heavily on **Daulton Varsho** (68.04) and **Cal Raleigh** (64.10). **Daulton Varsho** is particularly well-positioned, as Cecconi\u2019s defensive profile against the run game provides an excellent environment for him to chase stolen base upside, a critical need given our aggressive roster construction. **Lawrence Butler** also earns a strong nod (63.52) due to a favorable matchup against Rocker, effectively mitigating the penalty of his spot in the lower third of the order.\n\nOur most difficult bench decision involved **Drew Gilbert**, who finished at 45.62. While he provided the highest floor among our reserves, he was ultimately nudged out by **Jung Hoo Lee** and **Matt Chapman** due to their higher batting order security and the favorable wind conditions at the park today. We are tracking **Tyler Freeman** closely as his lineup spot remains pending; while his 56.77 score holds up, the \"Wind In\" warning at his venue poses a non-negligible risk to his power output. Conversely, while **Taylor Ward** faces a challenge in Early (2.34 xERA), his elite park factors and leadoff positioning keep his upside high enough to justify the start despite the difficult matchup. We continue to prioritize these high-efficiency pivots over bench options like **Gleyber Torres** and **Wenceel Perez**, both of whom are correctly relegated to the bench today due to poor platoon projections or unfavorable xERA matchups.",
